          %div.text-white
            %h3.font-bold.text-2xl{ class: "lg:text-3xl" }
              Debugging can be fun!
            %p.mt-4{ class: "lg:text-lg lg:mt-5" }
              Our web debugger takes you up where {#wtf?} left off: browse through operation traces,
              inspect ctx variables at any time and fix bugs within minutes, not hours.
            = link_to "Watch Intro Tutorial", "#", class: "base-button text-bg-blue bg-light-purple mt-10 mx-auto md:mx-0"
        = image_tag "code_placeholder_3.jpg", class: "w-full h-fit mt-10 mx-auto max-w-[22rem] lg:max-w-[26.25rem] md:mt-0 md:mx-0"
      .flex.flex-col.mt-16.text-center{ class: "md:text-left md:flex-row md:gap-16 lg:gap-20
                                                md:justify-between md:mt-[5.5rem]
                                                xl:relative xl:-left-[3rem]" }
        .flex.flex-col{ class: "md:max-w-[25rem] md:order-2 xl:relative xl:-left-[1.25rem]" }
          %div.text-white
            %h3.font-bold.text-2xl{ class: "lg:text-3xl" }
              Start drawing, stop overthinking!
            %p.mt-4{ class: "lg:text-lg lg:mt-5" }
              We're bringing the industry-standard language BPMN to Ruby! Model complex, long-running business processes
              with our web editor and let {trailblazer-workflow} do the flow control.
            = link_to "Watch BPMN Tutorial", "#", class: "base-button text-bg-blue bg-light-purple mt-10 mx-auto md:mx-0"
        = image_tag "code_placeholder_3.jpg", class: "w-full h-fit mt-10 mx-auto max-w-[22rem] lg:max-w-[26.25rem] md:mt-0 md:mx-0"
      .flex.flex-col.mt-16.text-center{ class: "md:text-left md:flex-row md:gap-16 lg:gap-20
                                                md:justify-between md:mt-[5.5rem]
                                                xl:relative xl:-left-[3rem]" }
        .flex.flex-col{ class: "md:max-w-[25rem]" }
          %div.text-white
            %h3.font-bold.text-2xl{ class: "lg:text-3xl" }
              It's ready!
            %p.mt-4{ class: "lg:text-lg lg:mt-5" }
              Sign up for free, check out how to leverage BPMN and our diagram editor in your Ruby code, and trace your
              code on the web. Then you decide how much PRO you need.
            = link_to "Watch Diagram Tutorial", "#", class: "base-button text-bg-blue bg-light-purple mt-10 mx-auto md:mx-0"
        = image_tag "code_placeholder_3.jpg", class: "w-full h-fit mt-10 mx-auto max-w-[22rem] lg:max-w-[26.25rem] md:mt-0 md:mx-0"

  %section.bg-bg-grey.overflow-x-hidden.relative
    .section-content-wrapper{ class: "max-w-[68rem]" }
      %div{ class: "max-w-[40rem]" }
        %h2.section-header.font-bold.text-bg-blue.text-left
          Future insights
        .bg-purple.w-12.h-1.rounded.mt-7
        %p.mt-7{ class: "lg:text-lg" }
          Picture this….you’re in your weekly meeting and you ask a question.
          %br No one responds. Whether they’re zoned out or are responding to emails or chatting on slack, it can feel defeating.
        %p.mt-8
          In order to have an epic meeting, you need five parts:
        %ul
          %li.list-circle
            Set a cadence for your team meetings
          %li.list-circle
            Have a clear meeting objective and agenda
          %li.list-circle
            Start on time and end on time
          %li.list-circle
            Have the right attendees in the room
          %li.list-circle
            Have clear action items [who, what, when] at the end of the meeting
        %p.mt-7
          Rate It was created to help leaders and managers have epic meetings that aren’t wasting anyone’s time.
          With timely feedback on how meetings can be productive, you will soon be holding world-class and
          super effective meetings.
